Preview a gt table object

Source: R/gt_preview.R
gt_preview.Rd

Create a preview version of table. Here we can specify the first and last n rows for the preview table.

gt_preview(data, rownames_to_stub = FALSE, top_n = 5, bottom_n = 1)

Arguments

data

a data.frame object or a tibble.
rownames_to_stub

an option to take rownames from the input data table as row captions in the stub.
top_n

this value will be used as the number of rows from the top of the table to display.
bottom_n

the value will be used as the number of rows from the bottom of the table to display.

Value

an object of class gt_tbl.

See also

Other table-part creation/modification functions: gt, tab_boxhead_panel, tab_footnote, tab_heading, tab_options, tab_source_note, tab_stub_block, tab_stubhead_caption, tab_style

Examples

# Create a preview of the `mtcars` dataset; it
# will be displayed in the Viewer
gt_preview(
  mtcars,
  rownames_to_stub = TRUE)
